              Open the managed path →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 rounded-[28px] border border-slate-800 bg-surface/70 p-6">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-slate-500 mb-3">Failure-mode evidence</div>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-5">
            If you want to see what inspect-only boundaries are protecting you from in real systems,
            jump from the trust-class theory into concrete provider failure paths.
          </p>
          <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <a href="/blog/hubspot-api-autopsy" class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy/60 p-4 hover:border-slate-700 transition-colors">
              <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">HubSpot API Autopsy</div>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Broad CRM surface, weak idempotency, and association complexity show how fast write-capable drift turns into operator pain.</p>
            </a>
