        <div class="mt-12 rounded-[28px] border border-slate-800 bg-surface/70 p-6">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-slate-500 mb-3">Fleet follow-through</div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-2xl text-slate-100 tracking-tight mb-3">
            Inspect-only trust is the start, not the whole operating model
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-5">
            Once the runtime graduates from inspect-only into real execution, the next operator questions are what breaks in the loop, how shared rate limits are contained, and how credentials stay narrow when the lane expands. These three pages carry the read-only trust story into live operations.
          </p>
